  "title": "Accessing Shared Network Drives and File Shares",
  "question": "How can I access shared network drives and file shares?",
  "answer": "Windows: Step 1 - Open 'File Explorer' by clicking the folder icon on your taskbar. Step 2 - In the left pane, click on 'This PC'. Step 3 - At the top, click on 'Computer' and then select 'Map network drive'. Step 4 - Choose a drive letter from the dropdown menu. Step 5 - In the 'Folder' field, enter the path to the shared drive (e.g., \\servername\sharename). Step 6 - Check 'Reconnect at sign-in' if you want to access it every time you log in. Step 7 - Click 'Finish' and enter your network credentials if prompted. macOS: Step 1 - Open 'Finder' from your dock. Step 2 - In the menu bar, click on 'Go' and select 'Connect to Server'. Step 3 - In the 'Server Address' field, enter the path to the shared drive (e.g., smb://servername/sharename). Step 4 - Click 'Connect'. Step 5 - If prompted, enter your network credentials. Step 6 - Select the shared drive you want to mount and click 'OK'. Step 7 - The shared drive will appear on your desktop and in the Finder sidebar for easy access."
}
